
Create a shipment.

See: https://google.aip.dev/133 (Standard methods: Create).

USAGE
  create-shipment <command>

ARGUMENT FLAGS
  --parent                           [R]  string               Resource name of the parent shipper for which this shipment will be created
  --shipment.origin-site             [R]  string               Resource name of the origin site of the shipment
  --shipment.destination-site        [R]  string               Resource name of the destination site of the shipment
  --shipment.pickup-earliest-time    [R]  timestamp            Earliest pickup time of the shipment at the origin site
  --shipment.pickup-latest-time      [R]  timestamp            Latest pickup time of the shipment at the origin site
  --shipment.delivery-earliest-time  [R]  timestamp            Earliest delivery time of the shipment at the destination site
  --shipment.delivery-latest-time    [R]  timestamp            Latest delivery time of the shipment at the destination site
  --shipment.annotations                  map<string, string>  Annotations of the shipment

CONNECTION FLAGS
  --address        string  Connect to address
  --force-trace    bool    Enable forced Google Cloud Trace header
  --insecure       bool    Make insecure connection (only on localhost)
  --token          string  Authenticate with a bearer token

OTHER FLAGS
  -f  --from-file    string  path to a JSON file containing the request payload
  -h  --help         bool    Show help for command
  -v  --verbose      bool    Enable verbose output
